projects.description:
DreamHack Bucharest 2015 took place, again, at Sala Polivalenta during 24th and 26th of April. It gather over 25.000 people from all corners of the world.

The network team's objective was to assure internet connection to over 300 PC/s laptops and for that my goals were:

* Designing and implementing the DreamHack Bucharest's 2015 network topology;
* Determining the overall bandwidth required;
* Determining the potential network threats that might appear during the event;
* Acquiring the required network equipments and components;
* Supervising the network implementation for FO and copper;
* Configuring all network equipments which provided internet access in all necessary areas. Such configuration included: BPDU Guard, ACLs, SSH, DHCP, PAgP/LACP, VLANs, MSTP, Port Security, etc.;
* Configuring certain Linux servers that served certain services (PAT, CS:GO, DNS);
* Testing network connectivity for all areas (Tournament, Partners, Press, VIP Lounge, etc.);
* Coordinating with the entire team to establish the proper Anti-DDoS implementation;
* Giving small inputs in regards to the configuration of the Super Massive 9600 (configuration made by Jody Spoor);
* Troubleshooting L2/L3 issues.
